'''Amber D''' (born 1982/3) is a British [[hard dance]] DJ from Staffordshire.<ref name=staffs>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/stoke/content/articles/2009/05/04/dj_amber_d_feature.shtml|title=DJ Amber D|last=Bosley|first=Kirsty|date=4 May 2009|work=BBC Stoke & Staffordshire|accessdate=16 July 2010}}</ref> As '''Amber D’Amour''' she plays [[electro house|electro]], fidget, and [[tech house]].<ref name=staffs/>

She has been a DJ since late 2001.<ref name=staffs/> Her first residency was at the legendary Golden, in Hanley Stoke-on-Trent, where she used to warm up for DJ's such as Tiesto, Armin Van Buuren, K-Klass, Mauro Picotto, and she then DJ'd on BPM Radio<ref name=staffs/> and at BPM parties.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/stoke/content/articles/2005/12/02/clubbing_bpm_feature_feature.shtml|title=BPM - a clubbing legacy|date=15 May 2006|work=BBC Stoke & Staffordshire|accessdate=16 July 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100804142201/http://www.bbc.co.uk/stoke/content/articles/2005/12/02/clubbing_bpm_feature_feature.shtml| archivedate= 4 August 2010 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref> In 2002, she won a DJ Competition at Fluffy, and started a residency at the club.<ref name=staffs/> She has released records with dance labels such as [[Tidy Trax]], Kiddfectious, and Riot!, and has DJ'd internationally, including in [[Ibiza]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/ibiza/article1060040.ece|title=She's Amber-Decks-trous|date=1 July 2005|work=The Sun|accessdate=16 July 2010}}</ref> She did an Essential Mix live on BBC Radio 1 in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio1/essentialmix/tracklistingarchiver1comments.shtml?20051009|title=Tidy Boys and Amber D live from Tidy Weekender|date=9 October 2005|work=BBC Radio 1's Essential Mix|accessdate=16 July 2010}}</ref> She was “Mixmag Future Hero” in 2004,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mixmag.net/content/amber-d-new-face-lacoste |title=Amber D is the new face of Lacoste |work=MixMag |accessdate=16 July 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100614232800/http://mixmag.net/content/amber-d-new-face-lacoste |archivedate=June 14, 2010 }}</ref> and one of her tracks was in the top 4 at the Hard Dance Awards 2008.<ref name=staffs/> She also had the biggest selling EP of all time on Tidy Trax in the shape of the Amber D EP that got released in 2008. She now runs five record labels, D'Amour Recordings (electro house), D-Day Recordings (Tech, Euro Hard Trance and Hardstyle), D'Licious Recordings (UK Hard House & Hard Dance), D'Licious HARD (Nu NRG and Harder House), and DirtyByDeisgn (Deep House / Tech House).<ref name=staffs/>

Amber is one of the most versatile DJ's, playing everything from Old Skool 90's Dance, House, Tech House, Electro, Jackin' House under her guise Amber D'Amour. Under her Amber D guise, she mainly plays Hard House, Hard Dance, Hard Trance and Hardstyle and Shranz alongside DJ Ash Preston as the "Shranz Project" depending on the gig.

She trained as a classical pianist and has a BTEC National Diploma in Music Technology. She got married to [[Lee Haslam]], another DJ, in August 2008, but they since divorced.<ref name=staffs/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thisisplymouth.co.uk/features/DJ-Lee-Amber-hit-decks/article-739234-detail/article.html|title=DJ Lee and Amber hit the decks|date=2 March 2009|work=Plymouth Herald|accessdate=16 July 2010}}</ref>

